DATAGRAMS</gmd:CI_PresentationFormCode>           </gmd:presentationForm>         </gmd:CI_Citation>       </gmd:citation>       <gmd:abstract>         <gco:CharacterString>Raw Knudsen KEB Datagrams collected simultaneously with multibeam                bathymetry and acoustic backscatter.</gco:CharacterString>       </gmd:abstract>       <gmd:purpose>         <gco:CharacterString>The National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), on                behalf of the United States Government, has a requirement to carry out surveys of                specific regions on the western insular margins of the Commonwealth of the Northern                Mariana Islands and Guam in order to obtain multibeam bathymetry. In addition,                high-resolution CHIRP seismic profiles were continuously collected and processed                during the cruise. These data are required to support any potential claim for                extended jurisdiction by the United States under United Nations Convention on the Law                of the Sea (UNCLOS) Article 76. The requirement is for the collection and processing                of full-coverage multibeam sonar data in water depths of approximately 1500 to 4500 m                in order to precisely define the location of the 2500-m isobath and the "foot of the                slope" as defined under UNCLOS Article 76. As part of their NOAA-funded research                program, University of New Hampshire (UNH) researchers oversaw data acquisition,                processing and archiving of the data collected during the                cruise.</gco:CharacterString>       </gmd:purpose>       <gmd:credit>         <gco:CharacterString>Center for Coastal & Ocean Mapping, University of New                Hampshire</gco:CharacterString>       </gmd:credit>       <gmd:status>         <gmd:MD_ProgressCode codeList="http://www.isotc211.org/2005/resources/Codelist/gmxCodelists.xml#MD_ProgressCode" codeListValue="completed">completed</gmd:MD_ProgressCode>       </gmd:status>       <gmd:pointOfContact xlink:title="James V.
